synonym.mean: 高的；长的；过分的；夸大的

word_mean_info__list.difference: 书面用词，指外观宏伟壮丽的高耸物；用于指思想或目的时，表示崇高。贬义指 态高傲。
普通用词，指本身高出地面之上，与low相对，不用于人。也可指程度、地位、声音等的高，还可作引申用。
仅指人或物的高度，指物的“高”时，可与high换用。

bilingual.source: Is she pretty or tall or short?
bilingual.target: 她是漂亮的、高的还是矮的？

bilingual.source: The path is hidden by tall hedges.
bilingual.target: 这条小路被高高的树篱遮住了。

bilingual.source: She is the tall girl in our class.
bilingual.target: 她是我们班上那个高的女孩。
这座建筑高的令人印象深刻。

bilingual.source: There is a tall building over there.
bilingual.target: 那里有一栋很高的建筑。

list.abstract: tall，英 [tɔːl]，美 [tɔːl]。英文单词，形容词。指的是高的，难以置信的，不可能的，身高，昂然的。短语搭配为:"a tall order(不合理的要求）"。 例句为：”This was a tall stone structure.（这是一座高大的石头结构。）“ tall比较级有taller，最高级有tallest。该词近义词有high，long。反义词有short。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you remember where we spent Mallory's birthday weekend? At Coit tower? Yeah. That tall cement nozzle thing on the hill. Exactly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还记得周末我们给马洛里过生日的地方吗？科伊特塔？是的 。就是山上那座高高的水泥喷嘴一样的建筑？没错。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, he's an Asian kid. He's an Asian kid, and he's not 7-foot tall. And you don't see a lot of Asian point guards making it in division I basketball.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他是个亚裔孩子，没有两米身高的亚裔孩子，你很少见到亚裔的控卫能进入第一分区的篮球队

yingyinNormal.en: Fine, but she's not that tall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，但她没有那么高。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll have a tall drip, extra hot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要一杯小的现煮咖啡，加热。

yingyinNormal.en: That tall guy, what's his name? Phillip?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个高个的，叫什么来着？菲利普？

yingyinNormal.en: That's not what I said. Tall cap triple-shot half caf?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我好像点的不是这个。小杯卡布奇诺 三份脱咖啡因对吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Back home, there's a girl works at the Wal Mart. Tall, tall girl. Woman could hunt geese with a rake.
yingyinNormal.zh: 以前有个在沃尔玛工作的女孩，长得实在太高，她用钉耙就能把鹅从空中打下来了。

yingyinNormal.en: I believe in tall, handsome strangers who hit on my wife.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我相信英俊的陌生人追我的老婆。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what else is a bummer? Tall guys with small penises?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道还有什么事很煞风景吗？大个子小鸡鸡吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I forget, is it the small hairy men or the tall not hairy men?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我记不清了，它是形容矮个多毛的人，还是形容高个没毛的人？

yingyinNormal.en: Beautiful, tall, sexy, showing her stomach? Look at all the boxes!
yingyinNormal.zh: 美丽、高挑、性感、露肚脐？你看这堆箱子。

yingyinNormal.en: And he was nine feet tall and he took my pants off and you said...
yingyinNormal.zh: 他有九英尺高，把我裤子都扒了，然后你说...

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, but one of those scientists is a tall, blonde Olympic swimmer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，可其中一名科学家是一名金发高妹的奥运游泳选手。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll have a tall cap, triple-shot half caf. Small scrap nipple slap half half.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要一杯小杯卡布奇诺，三份脱咖啡因。小屎尿屁一半一半。

yingyinNormal.en: Vivian, too tall. Madge, big gums. Too loud, too smart, makes noise when she eats.
yingyinNormal.zh: “薇安，太高大”“玛姬，牙龈太大”“太大声”“太聪明”“吃东西发出声音”。

yingyinNormal.en: Just a tall tale. Right. Because how could anything so miraculous possibly be real?
yingyinNormal.zh: 只是个传说罢了。没错，因为这么神奇的东西怎么可能会是真的呢？

yingyinNormal.en: How you doing, buddy? Life's a roller coaster, but I'm tall enough to ride. True dat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好吗，孩子？生活是一辆过山车，但我够高了，可以乘坐。同意。

yingyinNormal.en: A Cuba Libre traditionally comes in a tall glass with a lime wedge. Then swim to Cuba.
yingyinNormal.zh: 古巴利布瑞酒通常是用高脚杯盛放，并且杯口放上酸橙。那你游去古巴吧。

yingyinNormal.en: I would have been a great jockey if I weren't too tall. and scared of horses. Sheldon, you're up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我肯定能当一名好骑士，要不是小时候太高和害怕马的话。谢尔顿，该你了。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey Joe. You wanna shoot some hoops? And for the record, I am not covering the tall one this time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊，你要去打篮球吗？我得告诉你 这次我不要防守那个高个子。

examination_example.sentence: Central to hereditarian science is a <highlight>tall</highlight> claim: that identifiable variations in genetic sequences can predict an individual's aptness to learn, reason and solve problems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 遗传科学的核心是一个大胆的主张：基因序列中可识别的变异可以预测一个人学习、推理和解决问题的能力。

word_usage.usage:
tall多指由底到顶的长度，尤指比较细长的东西，如人、树、建筑物等。当tall与度量名词构成短语时，tall置于度量词之后。
示例：I'm six feet tall.
我身高六英尺。

examination_example.sentence: Rome's Colosseum was 157 feet <highlight>tall</highlight> and had 80 entrances, seating 50,000 people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 罗马斗兽场高157英尺，有80个入口，可容纳5万人。

examination_example.sentence: We'll pour about 30 percent more liquid into a short, wide glass than a <highlight>tall</highlight>, skinny glass.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们在一个又矮又宽的杯子里倒的液体要比在一个又高又细的杯子里多30%。

examination_example.sentence: There was no shade as the trees were no more than 3 feet <highlight>tall</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这里没有树荫，因为树不超过3英尺高。

word_usage.usage:
tall多指由底到顶的长度，尤指比较细长的东西，如人、树、建筑物等。当tall与度量名词构成短语时，tall置于度量词之后。
示例：I'm six feet tall.
我身高六英尺。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指人、动物、树木等有生命的事物“高”时用tall，不用high。
指建筑物、山“高”时用tall或high都可以，不过high的程度比tall高。
